<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="333" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,356,1136]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,428,453]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Shiny appearance, poorly pubescent, long rostrum, as long as the sum of antennomeres I+II, body small when compared with other 
<taxonomicName box="[525,743,464,488]" class="Insecta" family="Lycidae" genus="Macrolygistopterus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="333" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[525,743,464,488]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="333">Macrolygistopterus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species, costae I and IV apically fused, forming an arch, with elytral 
<number box="[230,244,500,525]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333" value="4.0">4</number>
/ 
<number box="[254,267,500,525]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333" value="5.0">5</number>
strongly obliterated; costa III obliterated at elytral 
<number box="[848,863,500,525]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333" value="4.0">4</number>
/ 
<number box="[873,887,500,525]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333" value="5.0">5</number>
; costa II reaching elytral apex, crossing the arch formed by costae I+IV, obliterated after the arch (
<figureCitation box="[705,790,535,560]" captionStart="FIGURES 27 – 35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1714,1737]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,204,1685]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,195,1693]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 27 – 35. Elytra: 27. Macrolygistopterus succinctus; 28. M. quadricostatus; 29. M. caeruleus; 30. M. germaini; 31. M. grandjeani; 32. M. subparallelus; 33. M. testaceirostris; 34. M. simoni; 35. M. kirschi Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271310/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="333">
Fig. 
<number box="[758,790,536,560]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333" value="34.0">34</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="333" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,356,1136]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,372,572,597]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333">Redescription.</emphasis>
Head black, prolonged in a long rostrum, as long as the sum of antennomeres I+II (
<figureCitation box="[1337,1422,572,597]" captionStart="FIGURES 10 – 18" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1433,1456]" captionTargetBox="[156,1432,198,1400]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1435,193,1413]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 10 – 18. Rostrum: 10. Macrolygistopterus succinctus; 11. M. quadricostatus; 12. M. caeruleus; 13. M. germaini; 14. M. grandjeani; 15. M. subparallelus; 16. M. testaceirostris; 17. M. simoni; 18. M. kirschi. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271308/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="333">
Fig. 
<number box="[1391,1422,572,596]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
); median interocular distance of 
<date box="[531,558,608,632]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333">
<number box="[531,545,608,632]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333" value="2.0">2</number>
x
</date>
eye width. Mandibles simple, not curved, slightly shorter than labrum, testaceous. Maxillary palp with palpomere I short, about 
<number box="[791,801,644,668]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[813,827,644,668]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333" value="3.0">3</number>
the length of II; palpomere II subconic, as long as III; palpomere IV truncated, transverse, securiform. Antennae with scape conic; pedicel with 
<number box="[1189,1199,679,704]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333" value="1.0">1</number>
/ 
<number box="[1210,1225,679,704]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333" value="5.0">5</number>
of scape’s length, other antennomeres missing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,356,1136]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333">
Pronotum pentagonal, wider than longer (
<number box="[680,695,751,776]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333" value="6.0">6</number>
: 
<number box="[699,740,751,776]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333" value="7.5">7,5</number>
), rounded angles, testaceous, with a wide longitudinal black strip; a pair of median elevations widened in median third; a pair of weak oblique elevations in median and basal region (
<figureCitation box="[238,322,823,848]" captionStart="FIGURES 19 – 26" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1260,1283]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,200,1229]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[150,1436,193,1239]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 19 – 26. Pronotum: 19. Macrolygistopterus succinctus; 20. M. quadricostatus; 21. M. caeruleus; 22. M. germaini; 23. M. grandjeani; 24. M. simoni; 25. M. subparallelus; 26. M. testaceirostris. Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271309/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="333">
Fig. 
<number box="[290,322,824,848]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333" value="24.0">24</number>
</figureCitation>
). Scutellum black, rectangular, longer than wider (
<figureCitation box="[888,968,823,848]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 9" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1834,1857]" captionTargetBox="[158,1428,204,1805]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1435,195,1259]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 9. Dorsal view: 1. Macrolygistopterus succinctus; 2. M. quadricostatus; 3. M. caeruleus; 4. M. germaini; 5. M. grandjeani; 6. M. simoni; 7. Macrolygistopterus subparallelus; 8. M. testaceirostris; 9. M. kirschi." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271307/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="333">
Figs. 
<number box="[952,968,823,848]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333" value="6.34">6</number>
</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[979,1011,824,848]" captionStart="FIGURES 27 – 35" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1714,1737]" captionTargetBox="[156,1429,204,1685]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,195,1693]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 27 – 35. Elytra: 27. Macrolygistopterus succinctus; 28. M. quadricostatus; 29. M. caeruleus; 30. M. germaini; 31. M. grandjeani; 32. M. subparallelus; 33. M. testaceirostris; 34. M. simoni; 35. M. kirschi Scale bar 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/271310/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="333">34</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,356,1136]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333">
Elytra subparallel, with lateral margins stout and pronounced, testaceous, with apical third bluish black. Arrangement of elytral costae: costae I and IV apically fused, forming an arch, with elytral 
<number box="[1168,1182,895,920]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333" value="4.0">4</number>
/ 
<number box="[1191,1204,895,920]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333" value="5.0">5</number>
strongly obliterated; costa III obliterated at elytral 
<number box="[515,530,932,957]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333" value="4.0">4</number>
/ 
<number box="[540,554,932,957]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333" value="5.0">5</number>
; costa II reaching elytral apex, crossing the arch formed by costae I+IV, obliterated after the arch.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,356,1136]" box="[199,785,1004,1029]" pageId="12" pageNumber="333">Width at humeri&gt; 2.5mm. Elytral length—11.0mm.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
